

## Add details to the config file according to the user created
##
## kubectl config --kubeconfig=config-demo set-cluster development --server=https://1.2.3.4:port --certificate-authority=fake-ca-file --embed-certs
## kubectl config --kubeconfig=config-demo set-credentials developer --client-certificate=fake-cert-file --client-key=fake-key-seefile --embed-certs
## kubectl config --kubeconfig=config-demo set-context dev-frontend --cluster=development --namespace=frontend --user=developer --embed-certs

## config file user private key, certificate and ca.crt must be copied to the remote location if --embed-certs is not used
